==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Housekeeping
<hw>House"keep`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of
occupying a dwelling house as a householder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Care of domestic concerns; management of a house and
home affairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hospitality; a liberal and hospitable table; a
supply of provisions.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tell me, softly and hastily, what's in the pantry?⟦br⟧
Small <qex>housekeeping</qex> enough, said Ph⟦oe⟧be.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Housekeeping</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Housekeeping
<hw>House"keep`ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Domestic; used in a family;
<as>as, <ex>housekeeping</ex> commodities</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

